==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: outspan
<hw>out*span"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>uitspannen</ets>.]</ety> <def>To unyoke or disengage, as oxen from
a wagon; to unharness (a horse).</def> <mark>[S. Africa]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>outspan</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: outspan
<hw>out"span</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of outspanning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A place where outspanning is done;</def>
